<DOC><DOCNO> AP880416-0141 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-04-16-88 2147EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i AM-Venezuela-Shootings     04-16 0251</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Venezuela-Shootings,0260</SECOND><HEAD>Venezuelan Marine Killed In Attack By Colombians</HEAD><DATELINE>CARACAS, Venezuela (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A Venezuelan marine sergeant waskilled and two other soldiers were wounded when Colombianguerrillas fired on their barge on on the Arauca River, the DefenseMinistry said Saturday.   Colombians fired on another Venezuelan vessel in the same areatwo hours later but there were no casualties, the ministry said ina statement.   The death is the first this year of a Venezuelan soldier in aborder clash with Colombians.   The fatal attack occurred when the dredging barge was clearing asection of the river about 360 miles southwest of Caracas. Theriver forms part of the border between the two countries.   ``A group of presumed Colombian common criminals in a canoe .. .opened fire suddenly upon the dredge, mortally wounding Sgt. LuisMalave Cordoba and inflicting minor wounds on two other marineinfantrymen,'' the ministry said.   The ministry did not say if the Venezuelans returned fire or ifthere were Colombian casualties.   Gen. Humberto Camejo Arias said military reinforcements havebeen sent to the area to search for ``foreign subversives andprobable accomplices.''   Venezuela increased its military presence on the border inJanuary because of an increase in kidnappings of Venezuelans byColombians and the use of Venezuelan territory by Colombian cocainegangs.   In January, Venezuelan soldiers killed five Colombians in anexchange of fire across the Arauca River.   The two nations agreed to coordinate efforts to cut down onborder activity by Colombian criminals.</TEXT></DOC>